        <h2>Returning Citizens Lead the Charge</h2>
        <p>Three Praxis <strong>Core Civics & Advocacy Training</strong> graduates have taken leadership roles in state policy discussions. Training participants have testified 47 times before legislative committees, secured seats on the Governor's Reentry Taskforce, and launched grassroots organizations. Our model proves that directly impacted leadership changes outcomes.</p>
        <p>The <strong>Drug Policy & Overdose Prevention</strong> team distributed 2,000 naloxone kits in Q1 2025 through community partners in Maryvale and South Tucson. We documented 47 overdose reversals and connected 89 people to treatment. Our latest report, "Harm Reduction in the Hood: Year One Data," shows peer-led outreach is three times more effective than traditional referral services.</p>
